"Solomon S., Daniel J.S., Neely III R.R., Vernier J.-P., Dutton E.G., Thomason L.W.","The persistently variable ""background"" stratospheric aerosol layer and global climate change",2011,"Science","333","6044",,"866","870",,,10.1126/science.1206027,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-80051664552&partnerID=40&md5=94dc60be64a71363f102f26662ad72bf","Chemical Sciences Division, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; Department of Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; NASA Langley Research Centre, Hampton, VA, United States; Laboratoire Atmosphères, Universitéde Versailles St. Quentin, Université de Paris 6, France; Global Monitoring Division, NOAA, Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO, United States; Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Science, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO, United States","Solomon, S., Chemical Sciences Division, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO 80305, United States, Department of Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; Daniel, J.S., Chemical Sciences Division, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; Neely III, R.R., Chemical Sciences Division, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO 80305, United States, Department of Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO 80305, United States, Global Monitoring Division, NOAA, Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO, United States, Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Science, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO, United States; Vernier, J.-P., NASA Langley Research Centre, Hampton, VA, United States, Laboratoire Atmosphères, Universitéde Versailles St. Quentin, Université de Paris 6, France; Dutton, E.G., Global Monitoring Division, NOAA, Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO, United States; Thomason, L.W., NASA Langley Research Centre, Hampton, VA, United States","Recent measurements demonstrate that the ""background"" stratospheric aerosol layer is persistently variable rather than constant, even in the absence of major volcanic eruptions. Several independent data sets show that stratospheric aerosols have increased in abundance since 2000. Near-global satellite aerosol data imply a negative radiative forcing due to stratospheric aerosol changes over this period of about -0.1 watt per square meter, reducing the recent global warming that would otherwise have occurred. Observations from earlier periods are limited but suggest an additional negative radiative forcing of about -0.1 watt per square meter from 1960 to 1990. Climate model projections neglecting these changes would continue to overestimate the radiative forcing and global warming in coming decades if these aerosols remain present at current values or increase.",,"aerosol; data set; global climate; global warming; measurement method; observational method; radiative forcing; stratosphere; volcanic eruption; article; climate change; data analysis; greenhouse effect; priority journal; radiative forcing; stratosphere; stratospheric aerosol layer; telecommunication; volcano",,,,,,"Hansen, J., Ruedy, M., Sato, M., Lo, K., (2010) Rev. Geophys., 48, pp. RG000345; (2007) Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis, Contribution of Working Group I to the Fourth Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, , Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, S. Solomon et al., Eds. Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge; Newhall, C.G., Self, S., (1982) J. Geophys. Res., 87, p. 1231; Hansen, J., Lacis, A., Ruedy, R., Sato, M., (1992) Geophys. Res. Lett., 19, p. 215; Robock, A., (2000) Rev. Geophys., 38, p. 191; Junge, C.E., Chagnon, C.W., Manson, J.E., (1961) J. Meteorol., 18, p. 81; Crutzen, P.J., (1976) Geophys. Res. Lett., 3, p. 73; Chin, M., Davis, D.D., (1995) J. Geophys. Res., 100, p. 8993; Brock, C.A., Hamill, P., Wilson, J.C., Jonsson, H.H., Chan, K.R., (1995) Science, 270, p. 1650; Vernier, J.P., Thomason, L.W., Kar, J., (2011) Geophys. Res. Lett., 38, pp. L07804; Myhre, G., Berglen, T.F., Myhre, C.E.L., Isaksen, I.S.A., (2004) Tellus, 56 B, p. 294; Hofmann, D.J., Rosen, J.M., (1980) Science, 208, p. 1368; Hofmann, D.J., (1990) Science, 248, p. 996; Hofmann, D.J., Barnes, J., O'Neill, M., Trudeau, M., Neely, R., (2009) Geophys. Res. Lett., 36, pp. L15808; Deshler, T.R., (2006) J. Geophys. Res., 111, pp. D01201; Vernier, J.P., (2009) J. Geophys. Res., 114, pp. D00H10; Vernier, J.P., (2011) Geophys. Res. Lett., 38, pp. L12807; Haywood, J.M., (2010) J. Geophys. Res., 115, pp. D21212; Kravitz, B., Robock, A., (2011) J. Geophys. Res., 116, pp. D01105; Ellis, H.T., Pueschel, R.F., (1971) Science, 172, p. 845; Dutton, E.G., Bodhaine, B.A., (2001) J. Clim., 14, p. 3255; Wehrli, C., WMO/GAW Experts Workshop on a Global Surface-Based Network for Long-Term Observations of Column Aerosol (2005) WMO Technical Document No. 1287, pp. 36-39. , http://ftp.wmo.int/Documents/PublicWeb/arep/gaw/gaw162.pdf, Geneva, Switzerland, available at; Thomason, L.W., Burton, S.P., Luo, B.-P., Peter, T., (2008) Atmos. Chem. Phys., 8, p. 983; Vanhellemont, F., (2010) Atmos. Chem. Phys., 10, p. 7997; See supporting material on Science OnlineSato, M., Hansen, J.E., McCormick, M.P., Pollack, J.B., (1993) J. Geophys. Res., 98, p. 22987; Ammann, C.M., Meehl, G.A., Washington, W., Zender, C.S., (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30, p. 12; Plattner, G.-K., (2008) J. Clim., 21, p. 2721; Gregory, J.M., (2010) Geophys. Res. Lett., 37, pp. L22701","Solomon, S.; Chemical Sciences Division, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), Earth System Research Laboratory, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; ema